name: C.CHRISTIAN 1872 WOMEN 50ml
campo_tres: Perfumes tradicionales cuyos nombres homenajean el año en el que la Reina Victoria otorgó su corona a la perfumería. 1872 for Women.170 rosas son necesarias para crear una sola gota de la preciada Rose de Mai, asociada con la pureza y la presencia de un ángel.
campo_seis: Traditional perfumes named as a tribute to the year Queen Victoria granted her crown to the House.1872 for Women. 170 roses are required to create a single drop of the precious Rose de Mai associated with purity and the presence of an angel.

name: GESTE EDT NATURAL SPRAY 100ml
campo_tres: La fragancia de la intensidad, con ámbar, almizcle, resina de pino silvestre y violetas
campo_seis: Powdered violets and a brisk musk that puts one in mind of freshly starched hotel sheets lead off this intriguing, elusive fragrance. Spritz it on and then go about your business, because it takes a few moments for this to come into its own. Geste is about the intensity of quiet things. The violets lose their powdery quality and become clear and sweetly melancholy, nestling into a comfy bed of amber-laced musk. Some musks are clean and some are dirty, and this seems to dance on the edge right between the two -- innocent and seductive by turns. Soft fir resin adds an appealing, distinctly modern edge. The resin has a hint of the therapeutic about it, like bath salts or a spa sauna, and adds a comforting roughness that counters the delicacy of the violets. Those contradictions – dirty and clean, rough and gentle – are what make this fragrance so fascinating. They also explain why this works so well on both men and women. Discreetly risqué, this has the genteel recklessness of an afternoon tryst in a luxury suite. Subtle and unique.

name: ASKEW EDT NATURAL SPRAY 100ML
campo_tres: La fragancia de la furia, contiene notas de Vetiver, alquitrán de corteza de abedul, cardamono de Guatemala, cuero suave, jengibre, mimosa egipcia y pomelo.
campo_seis: Inspired by fury. There is a bold swagger to the sharp, almost medicinal opening that puts one instantly on notice- stinging grapefruit, percolating ginger and the bite of something mentholated. As the fragrance develops, smoother elements such as soft leather and earthy vetiver come into play – but they never coax Askew into being comforting or tame. There is a crackling of static electricity like the air before a thunderstorm and the dark and brooding shadow of birch tar, which dominates the blend. A sharp and sweet gingered mimosa fizzes on the surface like the rakish grin of a con man. Dynamic and volatile, this is a classic men’s scent deconstructed by bad boy perfumer Christophe Laudamiel. He takes all the traditional elements – citrus, spice, leather – and tweaks them to create a fiercely compelling fragrance with an angular beauty all its own

name: MULTIPLE ROUGE NATURAL SPRAY 100ml
campo_tres: La fragancia de la locura. Notas de frutas rojas silvestres, naranja congelada, hueso de melocotón, piña verde, cilantro vietnamita, violeta verde y immortelle absolute.
campo_seis: Fresh and fruity taken to a strange and wonderful new level. Imagine a botanical Willy Wonka, creating the ultimate fruit in a hydroponic frenzy- a luscious melonberry, with hints of peach and pineapple thrown in for good measure and a dose of acidic tartness to keep it lively. The magical mystery fruit tantalizes -- one moment it seems completely familiar, you’re certain you know what it is, then it morphs into something exotic and unrecognizable. Cool, airy ozonic notes ruffle up against warm, velvety immortelle and occasional wafts of dry cinnamon and piquant cilantro float by. It is the Garden of Eden on a faraway planet – lush and delicious and a little bit alien. There is something gleeful about this fragrance – it has the breathless giddiness of seeing the dawn come up after an all-night rave. The dry down has a trippy, lighter-than air freshness that is tethered by a persistent murmur of warm, sweet earthiness – and that combination is what makes this so compulsively wearable. A fragrance to take you to your happy place.

name: CLEMENCY NATURAL SPRAY 100ml
campo_tres: La fragancia del orgullo. Con rosa, tilo, cassie absolute, madera, cuero, leche
campo_seis: Motherhood exalted in that most special of ways…by adoring sons. The reality of the giving nature of most mothers is little mud, some soup stains, crusty Play-Doh and maybe some yogurty lip blobs on the windows. Clemency takes a loftier path, looking to capture a mother as a figure of serene knowingness, a regal and proud figure amidst the chaos of nurturing a life. Rose is clear and familiar at the opening- the contrast of the sweet notes of acacia and linden against rich leather are harmonious rather than clashing. Woven throughout is the softness of a barely-there milk note. A grand perfume that spotlights the many faces of this woman-on-a-pedestal, from tender, generous, glowing and forgiving to proud, serious, stern and inscrutable, Clemency is a beautifully rendered take on a pivotal figure- the mother.

name: NEKTAR HAJJ 30ML
campo_tres: Created around noble notes, the appeal of Hajj reveals sweet fresh spices, such as star anise or ginger, associated with a stimulating background of warm notes. This fragrance with its original scent transmits all the richness of oriental perfumes. Enclosed by hints of various woods and succulent citrus, this balanced line gives the perfume a fragrance which evokes wisdom and spirituality. The notes include bergamot, mandarin, star anise, rosewood, osmanthus, licorice, ginger, patchouli, tolu balsam, tobacco and vetiver.

name: NEKTAR ASMAR OUD 30ML
campo_tres: Dusky scent, of earth and sun, of tanned skin and warm sand. A concentrated but pleasant amber fragrance, strong and delicate thanks to the careful blend of warm notes. A foray into the dreamy heart of a thousand and one nights. When Dorian Grey meets Scheherazade.' With bergamot, honey, carnation, coffee, amber cigar, grape marc, amber, tobacoo, chamois, musk and vanilla.

name: NEKTAR BURQA OUD 30ML
campo_tres: Like pure blood flowing, mystical and fluid, from every temple, with tones of Chinese ink and bewitched by essences of hard wood, this anthracite fragrance is a liquid incense with a notable prestige and elegance. With notes of jasmine, rose, black violet, cardamom, sage, leather, benzoin, myrrh, black ink, rubber sap, black amber, teck wood, patchouli and guaiac wood

name: PERFUME ASMAR OUD 60ml
campo_tres: Dusky scent, of earth and sun, of tanned skin and warm sand. A concentrated but pleasant amber fragrance, strong and delicate thanks to the careful blend of warm notes. A foray into the dreamy heart of a thousand and one nights. When Dorian Grey meets Scheherazade. With bergamot, honey, carnation, coffee, amber cigar, grape marc, amber, tobacoo, chamois, musk and vanilla.

name: PERFUME FAM OUD 60ml
campo_tres: An intense vibration of flamboyant red spices combine in perfect harmony with the warm woodland tones, in an embrace of powdery floral notes. Created by the genius of the Mughal emperors, this sophisticated fragrance exudes all the charm of Agar wood, associated with acanthus. Featuring saffron, chili, fresh rose, oud, cashmeran, rose powder, rubber sap, vinyl accord, sandalwood, cedar, milk and red musk.

name: SKARB EDT NATURAL SPRAY 100ml
campo_tres: La fragancia de la melancolía. Con levística, ajenjo, manzanilla romana, extracto de cebada, incienso, mirra y almizcle.
campo_seis: Skarb means treasure in polish and its the name of the first perfume by Humiecki  Graef. No other than the famous perfumer Christophe Laudamiel himself, prize winning 'enfant terrible' of the perfume industry, created this extraordinary scent. Humiecki and Graef asked Laudamiel to create a perfume that captures the state of 'how men cry' - eruptive and sensual. Pictures from Slavic culture, as well as how they deal with melancholia and happiness served as inspiration. The result is a perfume that combines raw eruption, sensual strength, melancholic warmth and deep mysticism. The form of the composition departs from convention as the scent is not constructed pyramidally as is traditional, but star-shaped. In contrast to the rigid categories of head, heart and base notes, the star-shape allows the scent to reflect deep emotions and the individual ingredients can be perceived. In the centre of the star is the core of the emotions: the feeling of shed tears. The different points of the star represent the facets of the concept: the watery and purifying effect, a deep slavic soul, childhood memories, as well as the soft and animalistic feeling of naked skin. The scents of absinth, myrrh, patchouly, sandal wood .... reflect in succession the melancholia upon with the perfumer based his creation.

No other than the famous perfumer Christophe Laudamiel himself, prize winning 'enfant terrible' of the perfume industry, created this extraordinary scent. Humiecki and Graef asked Laudamiel to create a perfume that captures the state of 'how men cry' - eruptive and sensual. Pictures from Slavic culture, as well as how they deal with melancholia and happiness served as inspiration. The result is a perfume that combines raw eruption, sensual strength, melancholic warmth and deep mysticism. The form of the composition departs from convention as the scent is not constructed pyramidally as is traditional, but star-shaped. In contrast to the rigid categories of head, heart and base notes, the star-shape allows the scent to reflect deep emotions and the individual ingredients can be perceived. In the centre of the star is the core of the emotions: the feeling of shed tears. The different points of the star represent the facets of the concept: the watery and purifying effect, a deep slavic soul, childhood memories, as well as the soft and animalistic feeling of naked skin. The scents of absinth, myrrh, patchouly, sandal wood .... reflect in succession the melancholia upon with the perfumer based his creation.
